---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import RelatedPosts from "../components/RelatedPosts.astro";

const metaTitle = "Enhancing Commute Comfort: How Swivel Seat Mechanisms Aid Cerebral Palsy Patients";
const metaDescription =
  "How swivel seat mechanisms ease transfers, improve safety, and boost comfort for cerebral palsy patients during commutes.";
const currentSlug = "enhancing-commute-comfort-how-swivel-seat-mechanisms-aid-cerebral-palsy-patients";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith("/") ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
const ogImage = `${base}logo.png`;
---

<BaseLayout title={metaTitle} description={metaDescription} headerVariant="solid">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <meta property="og:title" content={metaTitle} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={metaDescription} />
    <meta property="og:image" content={ogImage} />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content={metaTitle} />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content={metaDescription} />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content={ogImage} />
  </Fragment>

  <article class="article">
    <header class="article-head">
      <p class="article-date">August 18, 2023 · by vivek</p>
      <h1>Enhancing Commute Comfort: How Swivel Seat Mechanisms Aid Cerebral Palsy Patients</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="article-grid">
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>
          Cerebral palsy is a group of disorders that affect a person’s ability to move and control their muscles. It can
          cause a wide range of symptoms, including muscle weakness, spasticity, and coordination problems. These symptoms
          can make it difficult for people with cerebral palsy to get around, including during their commute.
        </p>

        <p>
          Swivel seat mechanisms can help to make commuting more comfortable and easier for people with cerebral palsy.
          These mechanisms allow the seat to rotate, so that the person can easily transfer from their wheelchair or walker
          to the seat. They can also be used to position the person in a comfortable and supportive way.
        </p>

        <p>
          There are a few different types of swivel seat mechanisms available. Some are manual, while others are powered.
          Manual swivel seat mechanisms are operated by hand, while powered swivel seat mechanisms are operated by a motor.
          Powered swivel seat mechanisms are typically more expensive, but they can be easier to use, especially for people
          with limited mobility.
        </p>

        <p>
          In addition to making commuting more comfortable, swivel seat mechanisms can also help to improve safety. By
          allowing the person to easily transfer from their wheelchair or walker, they can reduce the risk of falls. They
          can also help to prevent the person from becoming fatigued, which can be a major problem for people with cerebral
          palsy.
        </p>

        <p>
          If you are a person with cerebral palsy, or if you know someone who is, a swivel seat mechanism can be a valuable
          tool for making your commute easier and safer. Talk to your doctor or occupational therapist about whether a
          swivel seat mechanism is right for you.
        </p>

        <p>Here are some additional benefits of using swivel seat mechanisms for cerebral palsy patients:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>They can help to improve posture and alignment.</li>
          <li>They can reduce muscle pain and fatigue.</li>
          <li>They can make it easier to transfer from one surface to another.</li>
          <li>They can provide a sense of security and stability.</li>
          <li>They can help to reduce the risk of falls.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          If you are a cerebral palsy patient who is looking for ways to make your commute more comfortable and easier, a
          swivel seat mechanism is a great option to consider. Talk to your doctor or occupational therapist to learn more
          about how a swivel seat mechanism can help you.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="sidebar" aria-label="Products">
        <div class="products-card">
          <h2>Products</h2>

          <a class="product-card" href="https://www.trueassistech.com/products/turnplus" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <div class="video-frame">
              <iframe
                src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/nlMO30_RrKc"
                title="TurnPlus video"
                loading="lazy"
                allowfullscreen
              ></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="product-body">
              <p class="product-title">TurnPlus</p>
              <p class="product-link">Swivel solution for easier entry/exit.</p>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a class="product-card" href="https://www.trueassistech.com/products/turnplus-electric" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <div class="video-frame">
              <iframe
                src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ytQ7nRd8rf4"
                title="TurnPlus Electric video"
                loading="lazy"
                allowfullscreen
              ></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="product-body">
              <p class="product-title">TurnPlus Electric</p>
              <p class="product-link">Powered swivel seat convenience.</p>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a class="product-card" href="https://www.trueassistech.com/products/turnplus-accelerate" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <div class="video-frame">
              <iframe
                src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-bSUnSfkD-8"
                title="TurnPlus Accelerate video"
                loading="lazy"
                allowfullscreen
              ></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="product-body">
              <p class="product-title">TurnPlus Accelerate</p>
              <p class="product-link">Rapid, smooth swivel assistance.</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </article>

  <RelatedPosts currentSlug={currentSlug} />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .article-head h1 {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
    color: #451e5d;
  }

  .article-date {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--secondary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .article-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3fr 1.4fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .article-body {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  h2 {
    color: #451e5d;
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0.15rem;
  }

  p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-body);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-body);
  }

  .sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 80px;
  }

  .products-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: #fff;
    padding: 0.9rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .products-card h2 {
    margin: 0;
    color: #451e5d;
  }

  .product-card {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0.6rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    background: #f9f9f9;
  }

  .product-card:hover {
    border-color: #451e5d;
  }

  .video-frame {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: #000;
  }

  .video-frame iframe {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: 0;
  }

  .product-body {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.15rem;
  }

  .product-title {
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #451e5d;
  }

  .product-link {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .article-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .sidebar {
      position: static;
    }
  }
</style>
